        "paragraph_or_text_span": "This is a rare but serious bacterial infection that affects the tissue beneath the skin and surrounding muscles and organs (fascia). Early symptoms can include intense pain that is out of proportion to any damage to the skin, and fever. The most common cause is group A streptococcus.",
